ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Curbing child labour in the country. Addressing issues of children in distress and child health. Counseling and welfare initiatives with parents and children. World day against child labour campaigns. Child labourers rescued from hazardous industries. Advocacy for policy level changes. Mapping of child labour. Formation of state and district level task force for elimination of child labour. Raids & rescue of children from bonded labour. Core committee on child rights. Addressed the issues of child trafficking. Safeguarded vulnerability of children in natural disasters. Worked on issues of juveniles languishing in prisons of different states. Addressed the issues of children with disabilities. We have also filed many Human Right petitions / cases with the National Human Rights Commission and State Human Rights Commission. General Issues raised with the authorities: For sufficient wide roads, Flyovers, adequate space for parking and for proper transportation & for an organized traffic system, to maintain the congestion of traffic at Dahisar under the guidance of One Mass Traffic management programme. Raised the issue of up gradation and advance medical equipment for Bhagwati Municipal Hospital. Demand for play grounds and cultural centres to encourage the youth in sports & cultural activities. Advocated for Nana Nani Park / Health Centres for Senior Citizens. Made available toilets for people staying in small pockets of Dahisar areas. Establishment of a Centre for youth development. Solve the water problems of the growing population of Dahisar area. Established passenger assisting booths at CST & Dadar from the year 1994 till 2000 to assist specially passengers, differently-abled and senior citizens. Held several demonstrations to start new trains from Mumbai to North India & other parts of the country. Also held several meetings and demonstrations for the safety of women and children in local trains and also got sanction for setting up of CCTV cameras at all the railway stations. Under the slogan of â€œEveryoneâ€™s Mumbai Safe Mumbaiâ€ several programmes were organized for the cleanliness of Mumbai. Providing needy children with school bags, note books, pens, compass boxes and school fees. Organised several medical camps in the slum pockets of Mumbai. Distributed food grain, medicines, clothes, foot wear and other useful items to the Adivasis. Distributed food grain, medicines, school bags and other needy items in the orphanages of Mumbai. Distributed medical equipment and water coolers to various MCGM hospitals, such as S.K. Patil, B. N Desai, Bhagwati Hospital and many more.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Central India Institute of Medical Sciences (CIIMS), Nagpur, is a registered society (Maharashtra/215/83) and a Public Charitable Trust (F-3592) a dream 1966 of Dr. G.M. Taori, the founder Director, came true in July 1984. It is a medical research institute with a medical service wing (hospital) as part of infrastructure for research. At present it is a 114 bedded hospital cum basic life sciences research center. Research Centre has been recognized as a Research Institute by Department of Scientific and Industrial Research, Government of India since its inception. The major aim was to undertake research activity in clinical and basic sciences related to human illness. For the same purpose, CIIMS established a Research centre in 2000. CIIMS has well well-equipped Research centre, with all the modern amenities including microbiology lab, Cell culture and immunological and proteomics lab and animal house facility etc. Research Centre has elaborated 17 years research experience in the field of various infectious diseases like tuberculosis, including tuberculous meningitis, HIV, Neuroinfections, Chikungunya, Viral infections of CNS like HSV, CMV, Chandipura etc. and noninfectious disorders stroke and thrombosis. Research Centre, has developed around 20 advanced molecular and immunological methods for rapid and early diagnosis of bacterial and viral neuroinfections and identified novel prognostic marker for stroke. Published 100 publications related to various aspects of disease including diagnosis, pathogenesis, vaccine development, and new biomarkers for various diseases. More than 150 papers have been presented in different National and International Conferences. Adhoc research grants have been sanctioned for eleven of our research projects, five by Department of Biotechnology, two by Department of Science and Technology, Government of India, two by Indian Council of Medical Research, one by Council of Scientific and Industrial Research and one by Central Mine Planning and Design Institute Etc. The Institute has been granted two Indian patents for the development of diagnostic kits, one for the diagnosis of tuberculous meningitis and second for the diagnosis of extra CNS tuberculosis infection. A complete specification for a third Indian patent for the development of a thrombolytic composition using an herbal preparation for the lysis of human blood clot has been submitted. Research Centre has also been recognized for the Ph.D. program in Biochemistry and Microbiology in Science Faculty by RTM, Nagpur University and in Clinical Biochemistry, Clinical Microbiology and Medical Biotechnology in Medicine faculty by Datta Meghe Institute of Medical Sciences University, Nagpur. Total thirteen research scholars have already been awarded their Ph.D Degree (Eight by RTM Nagpur University and Five by Datta Meghe Institute of Medical Sciences University) in different subjects such as Biochemistry, Microbiology, Clinical Biochemistry, Clinical Microbiology and Medical Biotechnology. Research Centre, CIIMS time to time also conduct hands on training workshops in Immunological, Molecular and Animal Cell Cultural techniques for graduate and postgraduate students, researchers and teachers in life sciences and provide research services to research scholar in and around the Nagpur. Research Centre has collaborated with more than 50 National and International Institutions.
